<div id="c2">
<p>&#8220;Just because history has given you the power to choose whether this person can acquire certain material goods doesn&#8217;t give you the right to make that call.&#8221;</p>

<p>If I&#8217;m paying for the material goods, I feel like I should have a certain amount of power over what goods are purchased.  I have a moral opposition to drugs, and so therefore I won&#8217;t dispense money unless I know for certain it won&#8217;t be used for drugs.  Subsequently, I don&#8217;t give money to bums that are likely to use it for drugs.</p>

<p>When you ask other people for money without giving something in return, you necessarily give up some of your rights to privacy and the usage of that money.  See: Food stamps, etc.  The person giving the money isn&#8217;t trying to control the person receiving it, they&#8217;re just trying to make the most effective (morally and economically) usage of their money.</p>

